# Code owners.
#
# Every file has an owner so no pull request can merge without someone who
# understands the blast radius looking at it. Later lines win, so the specific
# entries at the bottom override the catch-all at the top.
#
# Ownership here means "must review", not "wrote it". The parts of this
# repository that can hurt someone are the deployment bundle (runs as root on a
# public host), the gateway (is the public host), and the claims in docs/ (are
# quoted by people who will never read the footnotes).

# ---- default -------------------------------------------------------------
*                                   @shark0120

# ---- things that decide whether a published number is honest -------------
/README.md                          @shark0120
/CHANGELOG.md                       @shark0120
/RELEASING.md                       @shark0120
/docs/                              @shark0120
/assets/                            @shark0120
/site/                              @shark0120

# ---- measurement tooling: changing these changes what the numbers mean ----
/tools/                             @shark0120
/tests/                             @shark0120

# ---- anything reachable from the internet --------------------------------
/gateway/                           @shark0120
/byok/                              @shark0120

# ---- runs as root on an operator's server --------------------------------
/deploy/                            @shark0120
/deploy/harden.sh                   @shark0120
/deploy/fail2ban/                   @shark0120

# ---- supply chain and release machinery ----------------------------------
/pyproject.toml                     @shark0120
/.github/                           @shark0120
/.github/workflows/                 @shark0120
/scripts/                           @shark0120
/SECURITY.md                        @shark0120
/LICENSE                            @shark0120
